description: To determine the impact of a low Mg(2+)/pH defined growth medium (MgM) on the proteome of Salmonella enterica serotype Typhimurium, researchers cultured S. Typhimurium cells in the medium under two different conditions termed MgM Shock and MgM Dilution and then comparatively analyzed the bacterial cells harvested from these conditions by a global proteomic approach.
title: Salmonella growth condition adaptation
